abstract: Corrections that appeared in print on Saturday, Dec. 21, 2019.
snippet: Corrections that appeared in print on Saturday, Dec. 21, 2019.
lead_paragraph: An article on Friday about the haggling and eventual agreement between congressional Democrats and the Trump Administration over the new North American trade deal misstated the stance of Representative Terri A. Sewell of Alabama on past trade deals. It is not true that she had never voted on a trade deal. The article also misstated the timing of a conversation Speaker Nancy Pelosi’s office had with Robert Lighthizer, the country’s top trade negotiator, and when Ms. Pelosi told the Democratic caucus “We ate their lunch.” Ms. Pelosi’s office informed Mr. Lighthizer of a news conference late Monday, not Tuesday, and the speaker talked to her caucus on Tuesday, not Wednesday.
